value: Formerly occurred over the southeastern lowlands of the United States from North Carolina to Florida and in the Mississippi Val- ley to southern Indiana and southern Illinois, extending along the coast of Texas to the Brazos River. Now confined to a small forest area in Louisiana and rapidly nearing extinction.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: formerly southeastern United States (east Texas north to southernmost Illinois, east to North Carolina and Florida)
